<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-502-355  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 502 355.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Oct 1 1990 v7 n40 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Furniture maker rolls out cost-cutting EDI network: net will alsospeed company's order processing. (Electronic Data Interchange)(Haworth Inc)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Haworth Inc, of Holland, MI, is one of the world's largest officefurniture manufacturer.andP;  The company is planning a worldwideelectronic data interchange (EDI) network of over 300 furnituredealers and suppliers.andP;  The electronic order processing networkwill speed order handling and reduce order processing costs,saving Haworth $600,000 a year by 1991 and providing the companywith an edge with dealers that also handle competitor's products.andO;The $400,000 system will process about 80 percent of Haworth'sorders by mid-1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Haworth Inc. (automation).andO;Topic:     Electronic Data InterchangeFurnitureOrdersNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>